 \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999505093923, \"rank\": 4.949061502989925e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Oliver\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 6}, {\"ngram\": \"a busy year\", \"from\": 41, \"to\": 52}, {\"ngram\": \"the game\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 123}, {\"ngram\": \"that year's Tailteann Games\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 169}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 198, \"to\": 204}, {\"ngram\": \"a chess tournament\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Held on the fringes of the Olympic Games in the French capital, it was referred to as the'Chess Olympics', though it had no official connection to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 240, \"to\": 400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9984131004358232, \"rank\": 0.0015084253454693472, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fringes\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 259}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 280}, {\"ngram\": \"the'Chess Olympics\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"no official connection\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 383}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organised by theFrench Chess Federation, the rules were fairly simple.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 425, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.303143276769843e-35, \"text\": \"Chess\", \"types\": [\"Q1914636\", \"Q11410\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 452}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each country could send a maximum of four amateur players to compete in the competition.\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 561, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each country\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 485}, {\"ngram\": \"a maximum\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 506}, {\"ngram\": \"four amateur players\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 560}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were to be selected by the national chess committee in their home country which would issue them with a certificate to confirm their amateur status.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 715, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the national chess committee\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"their home country\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"a certificate\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"their amateur status\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Ireland's case, there was a little confusion over which body would approve candidates who wanted to participate.\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998197695648463, \"rank\": 0.00018026279511017772, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a little confusion\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"body\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"candidates\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Firstly, there was theIrish Chess Union, formed in 1912 with representatives from all four Irish provinces.\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.303143276769843e-35, \"text\": \"Chess\", \"types\": [\"Q1914636\", \"Q11410\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999990654796239, \"rank\": 5.428926360058791e-07, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"score\": 0.9909931122468552, \"rank\": 0.008875646151478333, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"representatives\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A more recent arrival on the Irish chess scene was theTailteann Chess Committeewhich was formed specifically to run the chess tournament at the1924 Tailteann Games.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 970, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"score\": 0.9909931122468552, \"rank\": 0.008875646151478333, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A more recent arrival\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"theTailteann\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1004}, {\"ngram\": \"Chess Committeewhich\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"the chess tournament\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"the1924 Tailteann Games\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Letters even appeared in newspapers about which of the two organisations would best do the job.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Letters\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"newspapers\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"the two organisations\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1178}, {\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From TG4, Aonach Tailteann documentary on the 1924 Tailteann Games John J. O'Hanlon(no relation) from Portadown, Co. Armagh was selected to represent Ireland.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tailteann_Games_(Irish_Free_State)\", \"score\": 0.999999998966814, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aonach Tailteann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tailteann_Games_(Irish_Free_State)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tailteann_Games_(Irish_Free_State)\"}, {\"begin\": 1281, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\", \"score\": 0.6638756586635746, \"rank\": 0.48484848484842324, \"text\": \"O'Hanlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\"}, {\"begin\": 1308, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portadown\", \"score\": 0.8934852274242749, \"rank\": 0.11921268455974192, \"text\": \"Portadown\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portadown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portadown\"}, {\"begin\": 1323, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armagh\", \"score\": 0.998786362187998, \"rank\": 0.0008542223254700901, \"text\": \"Armagh\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armagh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armagh\"}, {\"begin\": 1356, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", 