://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\"}, {\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999505093923, \"rank\": 4.949061502989925e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"54 players\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1495}, {\"ngram\": \"18 countries\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"real championship\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"the amateur chess world\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1635}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has come to be referred to asthe first unofficial Chess Olympiad, yet another reference to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1692, \"end\": 1697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.303143276769843e-35, \"text\": \"Chess\", \"types\": [\"Q1914636\", \"Q11410\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another reference\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1745}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was held on the knockout principle whereby losers fell out and winners would play again.\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the knockout principle\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"losers\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"winners\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1820}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each competitor was awarded a commemorative medal and the winners took home a medal and diploma.\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1935, \"